<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
As Sprengel based his description on the exsiccata series collected and issued by F.W. Sieber, the best solution for typification would be to choose the specimen from 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Sieber’s">Sieber's</normalizedToken>
collection seen by Sprengel himself. Unfortunately, after the death of his son, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Sprengel’s">Sprengel's</normalizedToken>
rich herbarium was divided into many parts and sold in small portions to different specialists and institutions (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.48631" author="Stafleu, FA" journalOrPublisher="Zpravy Ceskoslovenske Botanicke Spolecnosti pri Ceskoslovenske Akademii Ved" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B26" refString="Stafleu, FA, Cowan, RS, 1985. Taxonomic literature, ed. 2, vol. 5. Utrecht, Bohn, Scheltema &amp; Holkema. https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.48631" title="Taxonomic literature, ed. 2, vol. 5. Utrecht, Bohn, Scheltema &amp; Holkema." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.48631" year="1985">Stafleu and Cowan 1985</bibRefCitation>
). The largest part, containing the collections of many botanists and among them also those by Sieber, was bought by B in 1890 (
<bibRefCitation author="Urban, J" journalOrPublisher="Zpravy Ceskoslovenske Botanicke Spolecnosti pri Ceskoslovenske Akademii Ved" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" publicationUrl="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/672page/664/mode/1up" refId="B30" refString="Urban, J, 1891. Der Koenigl. botanische Garten und botanische Museum zu Berlin in den Jahren 1878-1892. Botanische Jahrbuecher fuer Systematik, Pflanzengeschichte und Pflanzengeographie 14(suppl. 32): 9-64. https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/672page/664/mode/1up" title="Der Koenigl. botanische Garten und botanische Museum zu Berlin in den Jahren 1878 - 1892. Botanische Jahrbuecher fuer Systematik, Pflanzengeschichte und Pflanzengeographie 14 (suppl. 32): 9 - 64." url="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/672page/664/mode/1up" year="1891">Urban 1891</bibRefCitation>
), and subsequently destroyed during World War II. We found unequivocal duplicates of this F.W.
<normalizedToken originalValue="Sieber’s">Sieber's</normalizedToken>
collection in herbaria PR, W and JE, and as shown above also in PRC, although incorrectly labelled later by Presl. It is interesting to note that Presl based his later homonym 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. spinescens" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="spinescens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">C. spinescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on a different gathering (
<normalizedToken originalValue="Thomas’">Thomas'</normalizedToken>
collection), while he described 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. candidus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="candidus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">C. candidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on a F.W.
<normalizedToken originalValue="Sieber’s">Sieber's</normalizedToken>
gathering. As the above designated lectotype of 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. candidus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="candidus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">C. candidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs, without any doubt, also to the original material of 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. spinescens" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="spinescens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">C. spinescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Sieber ex Spreng, we designate it also as the lectotype of the latter name. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. Presl, Fl. Sicul.: XIX. 1826. [October" authorityYear="1826" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Cytisus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cytisus candidus" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="candidus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Cytisus candidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
C.Presl thus becomes a homotypic synonym of the prioritary name 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. spinescens" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="spinescens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">C. spinescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Sieber ex Spreng.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
This brings also another nomenclatural consequence: when treating 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. spinescens" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="spinescens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">C. spinescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Sieber ex Spreng. as a member of the separate genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Link" authorityName="Link" class="Eudicots" family="Fabaceae" genus="Chamaecytisus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Chamaecytisus" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Chamaecytisus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Link, the correct name is 
<taxonomicName authority="Link" authorityName="Link" class="Eudicots" family="Fabaceae" genus="Chamaecytisus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Chamaecytisus spinescens" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="spinescens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Chamaecytisus spinescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Rothm. This is because 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1002/fedr.19440530208" author="Rothmaler, WHP" journalOrPublisher="Feddes Repertorium Specierum Novarum Regni Vegetabilis" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="137 - 150" refId="B23" refString="Rothmaler, WHP, 1944. Die Gliederung der Gattung Cytisus L. Feddes Repertorium Specierum Novarum Regni Vegetabilis 53 (2): 137 - 150, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1002/fedr.19440530208" title="Die Gliederung der Gattung Cytisus L." url="https://doi.org/10.1002/fedr.19440530208" volume="53" year="1944">Rothmaler (1944)</bibRefCitation>
based his intended &quot;new combination&quot; on 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Presl’s">Presl's</normalizedToken>
illegitimate name, and thus accidentally published a replacement name (Art 58.1 of the ICN), which prevents making the combination based on legitimate 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Sprengel’s">Sprengel's</normalizedToken>
epithethon.
</paragraph>
